movies.title: Faust 2.0
movies.plot: Softwares and apps are daily installed based on agreements we scroll past and accept. But what exactly do we accept? In Faust 2.0 we meet five individuals who unknowingly enters into a pact with unknown forces and whose lives are brought to a brutal turn when they use the mystical applications to achieve what they want - but instead get what they deserve. As the applications spread the pieces fall into place and a digital pandemic takes shape.

biography.bio: Frida Liljevall is an actress, known for Faust 2.0 (2014), The Great Dying (2010) and Vägen Hem (2012).

biography.bio: Thomas Hedengran was born on February 11, 1965 in Nilsvallen, Härjedalen, Jämtlands län, Sweden. He is an actor, known for The Hunters (1996), The Invisible (2002) and Marianne (2011).

biography.bio: Per Burell was born on May 8, 1956 in Västerås, Västmanlands län, Sweden as Per Olov Burell. He is an actor, known for The Invisible (2002), Happy Christmas! (1999) and Executive Protection (2001).
biography.name: Per Burell

biography.bio: Per Ragnar was born on May 29, 1941 in Kalmar, Kalmar län, Sweden as Per-Erik Ragnar. He is an actor and director, known for Let the Right One In (2008), Storm (2005) and Korridoren (1968). He has been married to Veronica Ragnar (née Tigerhjärta) since 2000. They have one child.
